<h3>Course Description</h3>

This course is an introduction to the theory and applications of vector
spaces and linear maps. Topics include systems of linear equations,
matrix algebra, determinants, vector spaces, eigenvalues and
eigenvectors, inner product spaces, the spectral theorem and 
singular value decomposition.

<h3>Prerequisites</h3>

MAS 112 or MAS 261, or permission by the instructor

<h3>Text and Materials</h3>

<ul>
<li>Lay et al., <i>Linear Algebra and Its Applications</i>, 5th edition

</ul>

